cus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5828023\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ffc1705481850320.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ffc1705481850320.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ffc1705481850320.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"uuv1665702768330\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define an Application Server Shell\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Create a an application server shell when you want to define customized behavior for a Uniface server.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__context_w2367ab1b5b1_w2368ab1b5_w2369ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__topic_d12611e1_d12612e1_d12613e1\">You must have created a project to contain your\n\t\tapplication definitions. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hkq1665702549855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.\">Working with Projects</a>.\n                             </div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__li_d5909e1_d5910e1_d5911e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the U-Bar, click Browse, select <code class=\"ph codeph\">prj</code>, then choose the project you want to open.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__li_d5912e1_d5913e1_d5914e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Templates tab of the Resource Browser, select the Windows Shell template, then drag and drop onto the project object in the Structure.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__li_d5915e1_d5916e1_d5917e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__p_d12614e1_d12615e1_d12616e1\">Right-click the new application shell and click\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Open</span> to open it in the Application Shell Editor. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Notice that the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Shell Type</span> property is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">APU\n                  (Server)</code>.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__li_d5918e1_d5919e1_d5920e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set the Configuration properties for the application shell in the Properties Inspector.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__li_d5921e1_d5922e1_d5923e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you have defined global objects such messages and global ProcScripts, select the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Library</span> containing these objects.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__li_d5924e1_d5925e1_d5926e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you want to define your own properties, click the More icon (<img alt=\"more\" class=\"image\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__image_f5r_5t1_d1c\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/ellipsis.png?_LANG=enus\"/>) in <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Properties</span> to open the Define\n                     Application Shell Properties dialog. </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__li_d5927e1_d5928e1_d5929e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__p_d12617e1_d12618e1_d12619e1\">In the script editor, write ProcScript to define\n               the application environment and actions required to initialize the application. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example, for a web application server, you could use the\n                     <span class=\"keyword\">preRequest</span> trigger to authenticate the user before\n                  activating specific components or operations.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__li_d5930e1_d5931e1_d5932e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ghq1665702608876.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ghq1665702608876.html\" title=\"Reacts to asynchronous messages that come from outside the application.\">trigger receiveMessage</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__li_d5933e1_d5934e1_d5935e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uwh1665702683119.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uwh1665702683119.html\" title=\"System trigger for handling any global pre-processing, such as verifying the environment or user permissions.\">trigger preRequest</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__li_d5936e1_d5937e1_d5938e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bar1665702683338.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bar1665702683338.html\" title=\"System trigger for handling any global post processing, such as closing a database or writing a log file.\">trigger postRequest</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"uuv1665702768330__li_d5939e1_d5940e1_d5941e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span> to compile the application shell.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ohj1705472401504.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Application Shells</a><p>An application shell is a module used to initialize and run an application (Windows or character-based) or application server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/upi1665702529312.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Server</a><p>A Uniface Server is a server-based process that handles requests for remote data and component execution that it receives from client applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828023\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828023\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define an Application Server Shell Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define an Application Server Shell Create a an application server shell when you want to define customized behavior for a Uniface server. You must have created a project to contain your application definitions. For more information, see Working with Projects . In the U-Bar, click Browse, select prj , then choose the project you want to open. In the Templates tab of the Resource Browser, select the Windows Shell template, then drag and drop onto the project object in the Structure. Right-click the new application shell and click Open to open it in the Application Shell Editor. Notice that the Shell Type property is set to APU (Server) . Set the Configuration properties for the application shell in the Properties Inspector. If you have defined global objects such messages and global ProcScripts, select the Library containing these objects. If you want to define your own properties, click the More icon ( ) in More Properties to open the Define Application Shell Properties dialog. In the script editor, write ProcScript to define the application environment and actions required to initialize the application. For example, for a web application server, you could use the preRequest trigger to authenticate the user before activating specific components or operations. trigger receiveMessage trigger preRequest trigger postRequest Click Compile to compile the application shell. Related Links Application Shells An application shell is a module used to initialize and run an application (Windows or character-based) or application server. Uniface Server A Uniface Server is a server-based process that handles requests for remote data and component execution that it receives from client applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}